The hotel rooms were very clean and comfortable and the breakfast was continental and although not a great choice was enough to set you up for the morning.	The room was very small, even by Paris standards, although the bed was comfortable.	We had a twin room facing the street, (which was very quiet), decent sized bathroom, and spotlessly clean.	The room was small but very clean and comfortable, with a shuttered bathroom window - one could recline in the bath and feel the city just outside.	The rooms was sufficent in size, the bed and pillows were very comfortable.